text: Rosa Rush (1905 – 1971) was an American artist. She worked with the Federal Art Project of the Works Progress Administration (WPA). Her work is in the collections of the Metropolitan Museum of Art, the National Gallery of Art, and the Smithsonian American Art Museum. ==Gallery== Rosa Rush - Man at Construction (1935 - 1943).jpg|Man at Construction c. 1935 - 1943 Rosa Rush – Seamstress, c. 1936-42.jpg| Seamstress c. 1936-42 Rosa Rush - Tree Trunks.jpg|Tree Trunks c. 1935 - 1943 ==References== Category:1905 births Category:1971 deaths Category:American printmakers
